            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EGod%20is%20different%20from%20all%20other%20supposed%20gods%20in%20that%20He%20is%20invisible%20and%20His%20Word%20is%20His%20power.%20The%20idols%20of%20the%20earth%20are%20just%20senseless%2C%20speechless%20gods%20%22that%20neither%20see%20nor%20hear%20nor%20eat%20nor%20smell%22%20(v.%2028).%20By%20contrast%2C%20our%20God%20is%20a%20%22devouring%20fire%2C%20a%20jealous%20God%22%20(v.%2024).%20How%20important%20it%20is%20then%20for%20us%20to%20hear%20and%20heed%20His%20voice!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20centurion%20in%20the%20New%20Testament%20recognized%20the%20power%20of%20Jesus'%20voice%3A%20%22Just%20say%20the%20word%20from%20where%20you%20are%2C%20and%20my%20servant%20will%20be%20healed%22%20(Luke%207%3A7).%20Our%20faith%2C%20too%2C%20rests%20in%20the%20voice%20of%20our%20invisible%20God.%20When%20God%20speaks%2C%20it%20is%20with%20the%20voice%20of%20absolute%20authority.%20His%20Word%20contains%20the%20power%20of%20His%20ability!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhy%20do%20we%20look%20for%20tokens%20and%20trinkets%20of%20religion%20when%20we%20have%20His%20Word%3F%20Whether%20thundering%20and%20booming%20from%20Sinai%20or%20softly%20spoken%20from%20the%20pages%20of%20our%20Bible%2C%20His%20Word%20is%20the%20same.%20%22The%20Lord%20announced%20the%20word%2C%20and%20great%20was%20the%20company%20of%20those%20who%20proclaimed%20it%22%20(Psalm%2068%3A11%20NIV).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
